hondo717: ok, let me discuss my philosophy about weak 2s, which is different than other experts.  Many experts do not like to open weak 2s with an outside 4 card major.  and that is certainly a reasonable way to play.  However, I do not play that way. I feel that the advantages of a weak 2 far outweigh occasionally missing a 4-4 major suit game, so I believe you should open a weak 2 with any hand with a 6 card suit and 5-10 points  even with a bad suit.  Again, that is not the mainstream opinion, but I just happen to feel that my approach works out better. |
